    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring a numbers-matching 13B-REW power plant with verified high-compression rotors. This specimen retains its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, providing a linear torque curve with a seamless transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis maintains its factory 50/50 weight distribution, supported by an unmolested double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Meticulously maintained with an OEM vacuum-line refresh and a pristine thermal management system, this FD exhibits zero structural oxidation or panel misalignment. A concours-level example for the purist collector.",
